c.)\n   - namespace_policy.go: Namespace-scoped roles and bindings for kube-system namespace\n   - controller_policy.go: ClusterRoles and ClusterRoleBindings for all system controllers (kube-controller-manager, kube-scheduler, various admission controllers)\n\n6. **Policy-Based Storage with Escalation Prevention**:\n   - Role storage (pkg/registry/rbac/role/policybased/storage.go): Wraps StandardStorage with escalation checks. Create() and Update() methods verify users cannot grant permissions they don't have\n   - RoleBinding storage (pkg/registry/rbac/rolebinding/policybased/storage.go): Prevents privilege escalation when binding Roles. Uses ConfirmNoEscalation() to verify users only bind roles containing permissions they already possess\n   - ClusterRole storage (pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrole/policybased/storage.go): Prevents escalation for cluster-wide roles with special handling for aggregationRule\n   - ClusterRoleBinding storage (pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrolebinding/policybased/storage.go): Prevents cluster-wide privilege escalation\n\n7. **Escalation Prevention Mechanism (pkg/registry/rbac/escalation_check.go)**:\n   - EscalationAllowed() (lines 31-47): Returns true for system:masters group (privileged loopback)\n   - RoleEscalationAuthorized() (lines 54-98): Checks if user has explicit 'escalate' verb permission on roles/clusterroles\n   - BindingAuthorized() (lines 100-146): Checks if user has explicit 'bind' verb permission to create/update bindings\n   - All storage operations use ConfirmNoEscalation() (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go line 53-89) to ensure users cannot grant permissions exceeding their own\n\n8. **Support for Internal API Versions (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/internal_version_adapter.go)**: ConfirmNoEscalationInternal() converts internal version PolicyRules to v1 before applying escalation checks."
